<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>You can set the type of flash effect used when an image is captured, and test to see if the flash hardware is ready to fire.</db:para>
<db:para>You can retrieve this control from the camera object in the usual way:</db:para>
<db:para>Some camera devices may not have flash hardware, or may not be configurable. In that case, there will be no <db:link xlink:href="qcameraflashcontrol.xml">QCameraFlashControl</db:link> available.</db:para>
<db:para>The interface name of <db:link xlink:href="qcameraflashcontrol.xml">QCameraFlashControl</db:link> is <db:code>org.qt-project.qt.cameraflashcontrol/5.0</db:code> as defined in <db:link xlink:href="qcameraflashcontrol.xml#QCameraFlashControl_iid">QCameraFlashControl_iid</db:link>.</db:para>
